"{\"description\":\"To carry out specialised safety briefing and competency assessments of safety critical work for relevant staff and include outputs in the continuous assessment records of staff as appropriate.\",\"howToApply\":\"            html * {        font-size: 10pt !important;        font-family: Arial, sans-serif !important;      }              Salary:�28,000-�29,000Closing date:24th November 2023 - Late applications will not be accepted.Click apply now to apply.Drugs and Alcohol Standard:Our Drugs and Alcohol Standard is changing as of 16.01.2023. All prospective candidates who have not been offered a conditional role by 16.01.2023 will be required to undergo and pass a drugs and alcohol test. Your application will be rescinded if you record a positive test. All positive drugs and alcohol test results for prospective candidates will be securely held on Sentinel database and a 5 year suspension from applying for a safety critical role, a role which requires PTS certification or a Key Safety role on Network Rail Managed Infrastructure will be enforced.You can visit Evenbreaks Career Hivefor advice on accessibility support if you're unsure of the options available. Should you require any reasonable adjustments/modifications, pleaseadd a note to your application.Network Rail Benefits - To find out about what benefits we offer, click hereAll offers of employment are conditional upon satisfactory completion of pre-employment checks. Click here for more informationWe positively embrace flexible working recognising that employees might wish to balance work and family/home life.In Wales and Western region, you will have the opportunity to join PROUD, our reward and recognition scheme where you can say thanks and recognise colleagues across the region who have demonstrated outstanding values and behaviours.At Network Rail we promote a diverse and inclusive organisation. We are working in conjunction with the Cultural Fusion team to support black, Asian and minority ethnic colleagues. If you would like support with your application or interview please contact Wales&WesternCulturalFusion@networkrail.co.uk or visit the connect page: Wales and Western Cultural Fusion (sharepoint.com). For all other support please contact your HR Business Partner\",\"aboutTheRole\":{\"essential\":[\"Rules and regulations � level 2\",\"Experience of proven communication skills - written & verbal\",\"Presentation skills\",\"Ability to achieve appropriate assessor and instructional qualifications\"],\"desirable\":[\"Experience in front line operational delivery\"],\"keyAccountabilities\":[\"Develop, manage, and maintain a system that enables the briefing of relevant staff four times each year and which keeps a demonstrable record of attendance.\",\"Prepare lesson notes & materials as required in advance of all briefing sessions. Develop and utilise locally available simulation and computer based assessment material to deliver interactive briefing sessions.\",\"Custodian of simulator equipment and responsible for managing allocation of this resource to maximise effective usage.\",\"Carry out selected competence assessments of safety critical work staff as required.\",\"Professionally deliver safety briefing and assessment sessions with full consideration for suitable accommodation. In addition, provide answers to questions raised by those attending the briefing sessions in a prompt, accurate and informative manner.\",\"Provide assessment evidence and the associated feedback to line managers highlighting in particular serious deficiencies or development needs.\",\"Maintain hard copy library for controlled documents, manage appropriate access and distribution of documents as required.\",\"Undertake briefings of Rule Book, Network Rail standards changes and ad hoc independent assessments of competence to address route specific issues as identified by the Area / Route / Operations Manager.\"]}}"